# CareOn Operational UX Laws

CareOn is an **operational coordination system under scarcity**, not a healthcare SaaS dashboard.

## Archetypes (exactly one per route)

| Archetype | Purpose | Examples |
|-----------|---------|----------|
| `command` | Triage, escalation, doorstroom telemetry | Coördinatie / Regiekamer |
| `queue` | Werkvoorraad, throughput, row execution | Casussen, Acties, Signalen, Matching-wachtrij |
| `workspace` | Single-casus judgment and progression | Casus detail, Matching casus, Plaatsing |
| `network` | Institutional reference, capacity/dekking | Zorgaanbieders, Gemeenten, Regio's |
| `exception` | Audit, export, access | Audittrail, Rapportages |

Declare via `CarePageScaffold` `archetype=` or `data-care-page-archetype="workspace"` on workspace shells.

**No page may combine command + queue + analytics + workspace behaviors.**

## Laws

**LAW 01** — Only `command` (Regiekamer) may contain telemetry strips (doorstroom board, phase counts strip, dominant metric band).

**LAW 02** — Queue pages may not use `CareKPICard` or multi-metric stat grids in `kpiStrip`.

**LAW 03** — Every page exposes exactly one dominant next-best-action (filled primary or `CareAlertCard` / `CasePrimaryActionPanel`).

**LAW 04** — Matching explanations must cite engine output (`fit_samenvatting`, trade-offs, verification); no invented factor copy.

**LAW 05** — No fabricated demo scores, distances, or ranking when API data is absent.

**LAW 06** — Progress appears in one primary representation per page (timeline XOR doorstroom board on that surface).

**LAW 07** — Purple (`primary`) reserved for progression, focus, and primary CTAs — not decorative count chips.

**LAW 08** — Operational queues use `CareWorkRow` + `CareOperationalQueueHeader` (compact ~56px rows, inline right-aligned CTA). No full-width purple bars or hero-style case cards in queues.

**LAW 09** — One archetype per route; enforced in `client/src/lib/pageArchetypes.ts`.

**LAW 10** — No dashboard + queue + analytics on the same page (e.g. Rapportages stat grid + werklijst).

## Trinity source of truth

**Coördinatie → Casussen → Casus detail** define spacing, NBA rhythm, surfaces, and copy. Other routes inherit primitives (`CarePageScaffold`, `CareWorkListCard`, `CareAlertCard`, neutral `CareMetricBadge`).

## Verification

Run: `npm test -- operationalDesignLawsGuard`
